<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 29 日星期一 05:19:26 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Ex-Reagan Aide Massie Hopes Russia, US Leaders Will Find Common Ground for Dialogue]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110759390" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0c/1089858677_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_f0bceb5e739f3bf1813910e7ce4c15e5.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1089858673" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/ex-reagan-aide-massie-hopes-russia-us-leaders-will-find-common-ground-for-dialogue-1110759390.html?share-img=1089858673"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Maxim Blinov</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">美国驻莫斯科大使馆的俄罗斯和美国国旗。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Flags of Russia and the United States at the American Embassy in Moscow. - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="美国驻莫斯科大使馆的俄罗斯和美国国旗。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0c/1089858677_0:143:3072:1871_1920x0_80_0_0_a89bea0d042761c8588bf05ed990d0fa.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0c/1089858677_0:143:3072:1871_640x0_80_0_0_738f8d33e582a15222fee7d12f5e52fa.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0c/1089858677_0:143:3072:1871_1280x0_80_0_0_c3ab74a56cf5b5ea694010e5b5c4e0c7.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0c/1089858677_0:143:3072:1871_1920x0_80_0_0_a89bea0d042761c8588bf05ed990d0fa.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / 马克西姆布林诺夫</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：曾在冷战最后几年为美国总统罗纳德·里根提供俄罗斯建议的苏珊·马西告诉人造卫星，她希望俄罗斯总统弗拉基米尔·普京和他的美国总统乔·拜登能够超越前辈，为了“拯救世界”而同意对话。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “[俄罗斯、美国] 的总统过去可以交谈，”马西说。 “我希望现任领导人能够超越他们的前任，以拯救世界的名义找到对话的共同点……因为核战争的威胁是对整个世界的威胁。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">马西是在 1988 年里根与当时的苏联领导人米哈伊尔·戈尔巴乔夫在莫斯科历史性会晤 30 周年之际发表讲话的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">苏珊娜·马西 (Suzanne Massie) 为里根 (Reagan) 的莫斯科之行做准备，帮助撰写演讲稿。她回忆说，在访问莫斯科之前，她建议里根向苏联妇女发表讲话。马西提请里根注意这样一个事实，即女性回家后会对男性产生影响。里根通过电视发表讲话。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “戈尔巴乔夫问里根他如何喜欢克里姆林宫，里根回答说他喜欢一切比他年长的人，”马西回忆道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110759390" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/ex-reagan-aide-massie-hopes-russia-us-leaders-will-find-common-ground-for-dialogue-1110759390.html?share-block=1110759394" data-title="&quot;Gorbachev asked Reagan how he liked the Kremlin, and Reagan replied that he loves everything that is older than him,&quot; Massie recalled. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">里根还在莫斯科的丹尼洛夫斯基修道院发表了讲话。马西指出，这也是她的建议。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “基督教价值观的话题现在也很重要。作为一个开始，”马西说，并继续指出里根和戈尔巴乔夫第一次开始与上帝的话题进行交流。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110759390" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/ex-reagan-aide-massie-hopes-russia-us-leaders-will-find-common-ground-for-dialogue-1110759390.html?share-block=1110759396" data-title="&quot;The topic of Christian values is also important now. As a start,&quot; Massie said and went on to point out that Reagan and Gorbachev began communication for the first time with the topic of God. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">马西还回忆说，里根离开时，他告诉媒体，戈尔巴乔夫对他访问苏联的成功负有责任，因为他是国家元首。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">去年，马西与人造卫星分享了<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20221230/reagans-aide-warns-against-overestimating-soviet-union-underestimating-russia-1105904637.html" target="_blank">里根</a>的一封信，他在信中感谢她为 1988 年莫斯科峰会所做的准备工作。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">从 1984 年到 1988 年，马西担任里根总统的非官方顾问，作为通向苏联的秘密渠道。在服役期间，马西与里根分享了她对俄罗斯文化和人民的广泛了解，帮助他为与戈尔巴乔夫的会晤做准备，并为两国冷战的结束做出了贡献。她著名地教里根一句俄罗斯谚语“信任但要核实”，他在导弹条约谈判中反复使用这句谚语。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Massie 俄语流利，撰写了大量关于俄罗斯历史和文化的书籍。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 05:09:36 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/ex-reagan-aide-massie-hopes-russia-us-leaders-will-find-common-ground-for-dialogue-1110759390.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/ex-reagan-aide-massie-hopes-russia-us-leaders-will-find-common-ground-for-dialogue-1110759390.html<category>世界</category><category>罗纳德里根</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>苏联</category><category>我们</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Text of US Biden-McCarthy Debt Ceiling Deal Bill Released]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110758898" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110396867_0:0:3012:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_c1bc78de3e67ee2bbd1ca149e9499664.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110396849" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/text-of-us-biden-mccarthy-debt-ceiling-deal-bill-released-1110758898.html?share-img=1110396849"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / ANDREW CABALLERO-REYNOLDS</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">美国总统乔·拜登（右）与爱尔兰总理利奥·瓦拉德卡（左）与众议院议长、加利福尼亚州共和党人凯文·麦卡锡握手，他们在爱尔兰之友年度午餐会结束后离开圣帕特里克节于 2023 年 3 月 17 日在华盛顿特区的美国国会大厦举行</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="US President Joe Biden (R), with Irish Taoiseach Leo Varadkar (L), shakes hands with Speaker of the House Kevin McCarthy, Republican of California, as they depart after the annual Friends of Ireland luncheon on St. Patrick's Day at the US Capitol in Washington, DC, on March 17, 2023 - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="美国总统乔·拜登（右）与爱尔兰总理利奥·瓦拉德卡（左）在美国国会大厦圣帕特里克节一年一度的爱尔兰之友午餐会结束后离开时与众议院议长、加利福尼亚州共和党人凯文·麦卡锡握手2023 年 3 月 17 日在华盛顿特区" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110396867_0:0:3012:1694_1920x0_80_0_0_8e98ff00591756396abffb1b070e265f.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110396867_0:0:3012:1694_640x0_80_0_0_b504ea599308fdb553dc9b73666a5dd4.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110396867_0:0:3012:1694_1280x0_80_0_0_0653423e962b5830aa67963445f295ec.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110396867_0:0:3012:1694_1920x0_80_0_0_8e98ff00591756396abffb1b070e265f.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / 安德鲁·卡瓦列罗-雷诺兹</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">立法者公布了一项旨在提高该国债务上限以避免在 6 月初出现潜在违约的法案文本。该协议由拜登总统和议长凯文麦卡锡促成，将债务上限提高到 2025 年，并对非国防可自由支配支出设定支出上限。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，拟议的立法遭到了<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230528/republican-lawmakers-criticize-mccarthy-biden-debt-ceiling-deal-1110754135.html" target="_blank">共和党</a>和<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230528/debt-ceiling-deal-faces-criticism-and-uncertain-support-from-key-democrats-1110757454.html" target="_blank">民主党</a>的批评。两党的一些立法者都表示反对该协议的某些方面，这表明在众议院和参议院的投票过程中可能存在障碍。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <a href="https://docs.house.gov/billsthisweek/20230529/BILLS-118hrPIH-fiscalresponsibility.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">该法案长达 99 页</a>，包括几项关键条款。它提高了两年的债务上限，对联邦公共援助计划提出了更严格的工作要求，并取消了约 280 亿美元未使用的 COVID-19 资金。 2024 财年的国防开支上限为 8860 亿美元，2025 财年的国防开支上限为 8950 亿美元。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">值得注意的是，该法案保留了对退伍军人医疗保健的全额资助，并包括对补充营养援助计划 (SNAP)（通常称为食品券）中的退伍军人、无家可归者和前寄养青年的豁免。部分领取食品券的成年人的工作要求将暂时放宽，逐渐将年龄上限提高到55岁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该法案还旨在收回 300 亿美元未使用的 COVID-19 救济资金，同时保留用于疫苗开发、治疗、住房援助和印第安人卫生服务的资金。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国国税局 (IRS) 的资金将被削减，将 200 亿美元重新分配给其他非国防领域，并取消 2023 财年的总人员配置资金请求。该法案将要求借款人根据拜登政府的计划恢复学生贷款还款，同时维持以收入为导向的还款计划和潜在的债务减免措施。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 《降低通货膨胀法案》中的气候和清洁能源条款将保持不变，该法案将加快西弗吉尼亚州山谷管道的完工。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">众议院议长麦卡锡于周日晚间公布了该法案的文本，启动了众议院投票前的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230528/biden-says-bipartisan-budget-agreement-now-ready-to-go-to-congress-1110757999.html" target="_blank">72 小时审查期</a>。众议院最早可能在周三对该法案进行表决，随后由参议院审议。然而，由于立法者对该立法的规定表示担忧，因此从过道两边获得足够的支持可能具有挑战性。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">随着<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/yellen-us-has-until-at-least-june-5-to-hammer-debt-ceiling-deal-before-defaulting-1110618245.html" target="_blank">6 月 5 日最后期限</a>的临近，财政部长珍妮特耶伦警告说，如果不提高债务上限，美国可能会耗尽资金来履行其财政义务，这可能导致该国有史以来首次违约。参议院多数党领袖查克舒默警告参议院民主党人，他们可能需要在即将到来的周末工作，以确保该法案的通过，因为保守派参议员迈克李可能会拖延程序。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该协议是在拜登总统和议长麦卡锡指定的代表之间进行<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230521/white-house-accuses-house-speaker-mccarthy-of-presenting-unacceptable-demands-1110492823.html" target="_blank">谈判</a>之后达成的，旨在避免<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/the-final-countdown-goldman-sachs-economists-expect-us-default-by-june-9-1110611592.html" target="_blank">违约</a>和提高债务上限。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 03:50:35 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/text-of-us-biden-mccarthy-debt-ceiling-deal-bill-released-1110758898.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/text-of-us-biden-mccarthy-debt-ceiling-deal-bill-released-1110758898.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>凯文麦卡锡</category><category>民主党人</category><category>共和党人</category><category>美国债务上限危机</category><category>默认</category><category>技术默认</category><category>国债</category><category>债务上限</category><category>通货膨胀减少法</category><category>德克·舒默</category><category>国税局 (IRS)</category><category>补充营养援助计划 (SNAP)</category><category>珍妮特·耶伦</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Asiana Halted Sale of Emergency Seats Due to Open Door Incident]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110758491" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102108/47/1021084725_0:0:2500:1373_1440x900_80_0_1_3e26269427d8fabeb635170fc21e0e11.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1021084724" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/asiana-halted-sale-of-emergency-seats-due-to-open-door-incident-1110758491.html?share-img=1021084724"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / JIJI</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">一架韩亚航空公司的空中客车 A320 飞机在日本西部广岛县三原市的广岛机场冲出跑道后展开了疏散滑梯</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="An Asiana Airlines Airbus A320 aircraft is seen with its evacuation slides deployed after it overran a runway at the Hiroshima airport in Mihara in Hirishima prefecture, western Japan - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="在日本西部广岛县三原市的广岛机场，一架韩亚航空公司的空客 A320 飞机在冲出跑道后展开了疏散滑梯" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102108/47/1021084725_30:0:2471:1373_1920x0_80_0_0_675202ca42d6a3e6fc303bd1734aa428.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102108/47/1021084725_30:0:2471:1373_640x0_80_0_0_659ae954c26ad86c903cfab886d8ae88.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102108/47/1021084725_30:0:2471:1373_1280x0_80_0_0_9a91a5ef1816712eaf1ed0f21c59403e.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102108/47/1021084725_30:0:2471:1373_1920x0_80_0_0_675202ca42d6a3e6fc303bd1734aa428.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / 集集</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">韩国航空公司韩亚航空公司已决定停止销售某些紧急出口排座位，原因是最近一名乘客在半空中打开紧急出口门，引起乘客恐慌。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">事故发生在一架正在接近大邱国际机场的 A321-200 飞机上。飞机虽然安全着陆，但有几名乘客需要住院治疗，但没有造成严重的伤亡。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">作为对此次事件的回应，韩亚航空宣布将不再出售其 14 架 A321-200 飞机机队的紧急出口座位 31A 和 26A。该航空公司表示，这项措施是作为一项安全预防措施而实施的，即使航班已经订满也会适用。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>然而，目前还不确定这一行动将如何防止飞机上的其他乘客试图打开应急门。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">事件的责任人是一名 30 多岁的男子，已被大邱当局逮捕，并面临违反航空安全法的指控。据称，他因失业后感到窒息和压力而打开了门。如果罪名成立，他可能面临长达十年的监禁。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">媒体援引大邱一名警探的话说：“他觉得飞行时间比预期的要长，而且在机舱内感到窒息。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110758491" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/asiana-halted-sale-of-emergency-seats-due-to-open-door-incident-1110758491.html?share-block=1110758698" data-title="&quot;He felt the flight was taking longer than it should have been and felt suffocated inside the cabin,&quot; said a Daegu police detective as quoted by media."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">社交媒体上分享的视频片段显示， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/video-asiana-airlines-passenger-arrested-for-opening-emergency-door-mid-flight-1110619520.html" target="_blank">紧急舱门打开的</a>瞬间，空气涌入机舱，乘客的头发被吹乱。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">前大韩航空机舱安全官员金成贤指出，尽管乘客在飞机停在地面上时擅自打开紧急出口，但这种情况似乎是史无前例的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>一名交通部官员表示，男子之所以能够打开舱门，是因为当时飞机内外的气压相似。</strong></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 01:25:54 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/asiana-halted-sale-of-emergency-seats-due-to-open-door-incident-1110758491.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/asiana-halted-sale-of-emergency-seats-due-to-open-door-incident-1110758491.html<category>超越政治</category><category>病毒性的</category><category>大邱</category><category>韩亚航空</category><category>韩国</category><category>航班</category><category>紧急情况</category></item></channel></rss>